 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of 
     the visual presentation of the shape of mechanical design models. 
     Shape is projected into a plane display area. The projections themselves 
     are not represented, however the shape and corresponding projection algorithms are given. 
     Presentation attributes are included, such as line font and colour, 
     that may be applied to parts or all of wireframe, surface, and solid models. 
     Association of attributes with topological items is included to provide for 
     the styling of high level shape constructs. Advanced visualization capabilities, 
     such as light sources and surface reflectance are not included. 
   </p>
 </purpose>

